House Resolution 523
By: Representatives Willis of the 55th and Hugley of the 141st
A RESOLUTION
1 Commending The Links, Incorporated and recognizing March 10, 2025, as the Georgia Links
2 Day At The Capitol; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, The Links, Incorporated is one of the nation's oldest and largest volunteer
4 service organizations, founded in 1946, and is a not-for-profit corporation dedicated to
5 enriching, sustaining, and ensuring the culture and economic survival of African Americans
6 and other people of African ancestry; and
7 WHEREAS, The Links, Incorporated has a distinguished history of promoting the core
8 values of friendship, integrity, honesty, service, commitment, family relationships, courage,
9 respect for self and others, legacy, confidentiality, responsibility, and accountability, which
10 continue to guide its efforts to empower communities across the country; and
11 WHEREAS, the members of The Links, Incorporated are influential decision-makers and
12 opinion leaders, including business and civic leaders, role models, mentors, activists, and
13 volunteers dedicated to making a positive difference in their communities and the world; and
