14 WHEREAS, The Links, Incorporated contributes more than one million documented hours
15 of community service annually, thereby strengthening local communities and enhancing the
16 well-being of the nation; and
17 WHEREAS, The Links, Incorporated has a comprehensive and impactful programmatic
18 focus, which includes five key areas: Services to Youth, The Arts, National Trends and
19 Services, International Trends and Services, and Health and Human Services, all of which
20 are implemented through public information, education, economic development, and public
21 policy campaigns.
22 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
23 the members of this body commend The Links, Incorporated for its unwavering commitment
24 to service and leadership and recognize March 10, 2025, as Georgia Links Day At The
25 Capitol in honor of their outstanding contributions to society.
26 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
27 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to The
28 Links, Incorporated.
